==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Condiment
<hw>Con"di*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>condimentum</ets>, fr. <ets>condire</ets>. See
<er>Condite</er>.]</ety> <def>Something used to give relish to food, and
to gratify the taste; a pungent and appetizing substance, as pepper or
mustard; seasoning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As for radish and the like, they are for <qex>condiments</qex>,
and not for nourishment.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Condisciple</ent>⟦br⟧
